    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-15T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="738"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–1552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WAM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d738fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to New
                        Delhi and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-15T15:00:00+05:00"
                            >August 15, 1952—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>214. Last night I delivered orally to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss> in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>
                    239 Aug 12.<note n="2" xml:id="d738fn2">The same as telegram 422 to New Delhi,
                            <ref target="#d737">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrulla</persName> expressed his pleasure and at
                    same time his doubts that Geneva mtg will achieve any marked success. He said
                    his own intention is to support <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>’s
                    proposals with complete sincerity and to the limit. He has obtained from Cab
                    approval to negotiate on minimum figs for both sides mentioned in <persName
                        corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>’s invitation.</p>
                <p>He added as last thought hope that <gloss target="#t_Pres1">Pres</gloss> and UK
                        <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> will express their interest in a
                    succeseful mtg shld there be indication of it going on rocks.</p>
                <p>This morning when UK <gloss target="#t_HICOM1">HICOM</gloss> talked with me at
                    our usual weekly mtg he said <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1">Zafrulla</persName>
                    had mentioned to him last night my message and that Laithwaite on his own had
                    expressed gratification that two govts have decided to send Mins to Geneva. He
                    added it is his own personal hope that the conf may have successful results. In
                    commenting this morning on his conversation with <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1"
                        >Zafrulla</persName>, Laithwaite said he did not feel free to mention his
                    govt org <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1"
                        >Zafrulla</persName> in talking with him had expressed more or less same
                    thoughts he had given me earlier in evening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WAM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
